title: Test
summary: This line chart has an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Unemployment rate, with a total of 21 data points.
Overall Unemployment rate has increased over the Year.

Unemployment rate is slightly decreasing from 1999 to 2000, gradually increasing from 2000 to 2002, roughly constant from 2002 to 2005, slightly decreasing from 2005 to 2006, roughly constant from 2006 to 2007, gradually increasing from 2007 to 2009, slightly decreasing from 2009 to 2011, slightly increasing from 2011 to 2014, roughly constant from 2014 to 2018, and lastly roughly increasing from 2018 to 2019.
The steepest increase occurs in between the Year 2008 and 2009.
Max Unemployment rate about 12.55 was recorded at Year 2009
Min Unemployment rate about 6.5 was recorded at Year 2000
This line chart has an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Unemployment rate, with a total of 21 data points. The chart has 5 significant trends.
The longest trend is moderately increasing which exists from 1999 to 2006.
In a similar manner, the next significant trend is extremely increasing which exists from 2012 to 2016.
Additionally, the next significant trend is moderately decreasing which exists from 2016 to 2019.
Contrarily, the next significant trend is slightly decreasing which exists from 2009 to 2012.
Conversely, the next significant trend is extremely increasing which exists from 2006 to 2009.
